text: "Rated "X"" is a 1972 song by country singer Loretta Lynn. It was taken from her 22nd studio album Entertainer of the Year. It topped the country singles charts in both the United States and Canada. It was covered by The White Stripes as a B-side to their single Hotel Yorba in 2001.
